Dial.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.871
I should've brought
my rubber nose.

04:45.485 --> 04:46.975
(phone ringing)

04:47.120 --> 04:48.417
MARION:
I'll get it.

04:50.457 --> 04:51.390
Hello.

04:51.525 --> 04:53.516
Oh, hello, Ralph.

04:53.660 --> 04:56.129
Howard, he called me Mom.

04:56.263 --> 04:58.254
Who called you Mom?

04:59.833 --> 05:02.666
Well, Ralph Malph, dear.

05:02.803 --> 05:04.794
What is it, Ralph?

05:04.938 --> 05:07.236
- He did it again, Howard.
- Okay, let me...

05:07.374 --> 05:09.001
Ralph, what's going on?

05:09.142 --> 05:11.201
He just called me Dad.

05:12.612 --> 05:15.638
Look, Ralph, will you
stop clowning and...

05:15.782 --> 05:16.908
What's that?

05:17.050 --> 05:19.212
You won't be home tonight?

05:19.352 --> 05:21.912
And Potsie won't
be home tonight.

05:22.055 --> 05:25.355
And your nose hurts.

05:25.492 --> 05:27.722
All right, good night, son.

05:27.861 --> 05:30.296
What am I saying?

05:31.464 --> 05:33.694
MARION:
Oh, Arthur, look at you!

05:33.834 --> 05:36.064
Richard, what happened?

05:36.203 --> 05:37.728
There was a blast tonight.

05:37.871 --> 05:41.102
You two, you always have such
a good time together.

05:41.241 --> 05:44.438
Mr. C., Mrs. C.,
let me tell you something.

05:44.578 --> 05:46.068
Your son's talking the truth.

05:46.213 --> 05:47.908
We're talking boomsville,
you know?

05:48.048 --> 05:50.676
Glass shattering, smoke.

05:50.817 --> 05:53.184
The counterfeiters tried
to blow up Fonzie's garage

05:53.320 --> 05:54.378
with Fonzie in it.

05:54.521 --> 05:56.011
Well, now how do you know
it was them?

05:56.156 --> 05:57.282
Tell them, Rich.

05:57.424 --> 05:58.448
Because I overheard them

05:58.592 --> 06:00.185
when I was laying
in the casket, Dad.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.390
Blown up, casket...

06:03.530 --> 06:05.430
Oh, this is such
a confusing night.

06:05.565 --> 06:07.329
Now will you just start
from the beginning?

06:07.467 --> 06:09.196
No, Mom, no, I got to call
the police now.

06:09.336 --> 06:10.997
- Yeah. -I'm gonna reheat
the hot chocolate.

06:11.137 --> 06:13.299
That's what I do the best
when things are confusing.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.240
From the looks of Fonzie,

06:16.376 --> 06:18.037
he needs something
a lot stronger.

06:18.178 --> 06:19.202
You're not kidding.

06:19.346 --> 06:20.711
Those small marshmallows.

06:20.847 --> 06:22.713
Oh, they're in the,
in the cupboard there, Arthur.

06:22.849 --> 06:24.476
- Yeah.
-(doorbell rings)

06:24.618 --> 06:26.450
Oh, Jiminy Crickets, what now?

06:26.586 --> 06:28.714
Hello, Operator,
I need the police.

06:28.855 --> 06:29.947
Uh, Peterson, Treasury.

06:30.090 --> 06:32.149
Yes, I know, I know.
Come on in, Mr. Peterson.

06:32.292 --> 06:33.987
Oh, this is my son Richard.

06:34.127 --> 06:35.891
Richard, this is Mr. Peterson
of the Treasury Department.

06:36.029 --> 06:37.155
Uh, Peterson, Treasury.

06:37.297 --> 06:38.458
Oh, hi.

06:38.598 --> 06:40.464
Well, thanks anyway,
but I got a T-man.

06:40.600 --> 06:42.568
Oh, boy, am I glad to see you.

06:42.702 --> 06:45.433
Uh, uh, please,
I have a sad duty to perform.

06:45.572 --> 06:47.973
Arthur Fonzarelli was blown up.

06:48.108 --> 06:49.234
If it's any consolation,

06:49.376 --> 06:51.242
I assure you
he-he didn't suffer.

06:51.378 --> 06:52.846
He merely died.

06:52.979 --> 06:54.640
Hey, want some hot chocolate?

06:54.781 --> 06:56.647
- Uh, no thanks, I'm on duty.
- Oh, all right.

06:56.783 --> 06:58.547
It's a good thing 'cause
it's got marshmallows in it.

06:58.685 --> 07:00.483
You!
"Me!

07:00.620 --> 07:01.610
You're alive!

07:01.755 --> 07:02.916
What was your first clue?

07:03.056 --> 07:04.285
But how?

07:04.424 --> 07:05.789
H ow?

07:05.926 --> 07:07.621
He was standing
behind his address book

07:07.761 --> 07:08.990
at the time of the explosion.

07:09.129 --> 07:10.619
One little address book?

07:10.764 --> 07:14.826
Nah, six four-drawer
steel filing cabinets.

07:14.968 --> 07:17.300
Fonzie knows a lot of girls.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.906
Oh, I figured it out.

07:20.040 --> 07:21.565
Yes, I know, Peterson.

07:21.708 --> 07:24.234
Nice picture.

07:24.377 --> 07:25.970
You figured what out,
sweetheart?

07:26.112 --> 07:27.944
Ralph and Potsie's phone call.

07:28.081 --> 07:29.139
What about Ralph and Potsie?

07:29.282 --> 07:30.443
Oh, Ralph called up here

07:30.583 --> 07:32.381
pretending
he was Ralph Cunningham.

07:32.519 --> 07:33.953
- It's not important.
- Yes, it is.

07:34.087 --> 07:36.556
They went with me to the
Heavenly Slumber Funeral Parlor.

07:36.690 --> 07:38.454
Now, now, Fonz, you don't
suppose that they, uh...

07:38.591 --> 07:40.582
They got their hands
on Ralph and Potsie, right?

07:40.727 --> 07:42.058
- Right.
- We're going down there.

07:42.195 --> 07:44.289
We're gonna add three more
stiffs to their inventory.

07:44.431 --> 07:45.990
- Yeah, that's a good idea.
- No.

07:46.132 --> 07:47.327
- No?
- No.

07:47.467 --> 07:48.957
Thanks a lot, T-man.

07:49.102 --> 07:50.570
All right, look,

07:50.704 --> 07:51.899
Candy Man thinks I'm dead,
right?

07:52.038 --> 07:53.267
- Right.
- All right.

07:53.406 --> 07:55.067
What's the best way to get
into a funeral parlor?

07:55.208 --> 07:57.677
Having a funeral,
even if it is mine.

07:57.811 --> 07:59.779
- We catch Candy Man
with the goods. -Right.

07:59.913 --> 08:02.109
We save Ralph and Potsie and,
you know,

08:02.248 --> 08:03.579
they were saying that they want

08:03.717 --> 08:04.878
their next shipment
to go to Detroit.

08:05.018 --> 08:06.417
That's great, Rich.

08:06.553 --> 08:08.681
Look, we just tell them
that our loved one,

08:08.822 --> 08:10.551
which happens to be me,
(chuckles)

08:10.690 --> 08:13.523
wants to be buried in Detroit.

08:13.660 --> 08:14.684
Great plan.

08:14.828 --> 08:15.954
Now, wait a minute.

08:16.096 --> 08:17.359
I'll admit
that it's a good plan,

08:17.497 --> 08:18.965
but, you know,
it could be very dangerous.

08:19.099 --> 08:20.157
It's for your country.

08:20.300 --> 08:21.961
Dad, look, Ralph and Potsie

08:22.102 --> 08:24.161
are in trouble and look
what they did to Fonzie.

08:24.304 --> 08:26.534
Yeah, they mussed my hair.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.471
Besides, you guys are gonna
have the funeral parlor

08:28.608 --> 08:29.871
under surveillance
at all times, right?

08:30.010 --> 08:31.068
PETERSON:
That's right.

08:31.211 --> 08:33.509
Well, why not?

08:33.645 --> 08:35.239
We're such good citizens.

08:35.381 --> 08:36.474
One last thing.

08:36.616 --> 08:39.176
No one must know
that Fonzarelli's alive.

08:39.318 --> 08:40.878
No one outside
this house can know.

08:41.020 --> 08:42.921
That funeral has to look
as real as possible.

08:43.056 --> 08:46.583
If the Candy Man finds out,
we're all in a lot of danger.

08:46.726 --> 08:49.320
BOTH:
Candy Man.

08:52.332 --> 08:56.394
Candy Man, we should finish
printing the money by 1:00.

08:56.536 --> 08:57.435
Perfect.

08:57.570 --> 08:59.561
The train to Detroit
leaves at 4:00.

08:59.706 --> 09:01.333
Boss, how're we gonna send
the shipment?

09:01.474 --> 09:03.135
We ain't got a body
in the coffin.

09:03.276 --> 09:04.539
MARION:
Yoo-hoo!

09:04.677 --> 09:06.042
Anybody home?

09:10.717 --> 09:12.481
Hi.

09:12.619 --> 09:14.883
We'd like to bury a friend.

09:16.823 --> 09:18.917
My assistant will be glad
to show you

09:19.059 --> 09:20.493
to another funeral parlor.

09:20.627 --> 09:22.652
We're all booked up.

09:22.796 --> 09:24.321
Oh, it would be
a very short ceremony.

09:24.464 --> 09:26.762
The actual burial would be
in Detroit.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.425
- Detroit! -Detroit.
- Detroit!

09:28.568 --> 09:31.060
- Detroit.
-(cackles)

09:31.204 --> 09:33.764
Perhaps we could fit you in.

09:33.907 --> 09:36.604
EUGENE:
Uh, where is the loved one?

09:36.743 --> 09:38.768
Well, he's in here.

09:38.912 --> 09:39.936
ALL:
In there?!

09:40.080 --> 09:41.605
There was an explosion.

09:41.748 --> 09:44.410
This is all that's left
of Arthur Fonzarelli.

09:44.551 --> 09:45.484
Fonza...

09:45.618 --> 09:47.086
ALL:
...relli.

09:49.155 --> 09:50.816
We'd like to have
the funeral fast.

09:50.957 --> 09:52.891
- Right away.
- Right away?

09:53.026 --> 09:54.551
Well, there should be
a period of mourning.

09:54.694 --> 09:55.718
You're right, dear.

09:55.862 --> 09:57.057
How about after lunch?

09:57.197 --> 09:58.665
Perfect. (chuckles)

09:58.798 --> 10:01.597
My assistant will give you
all the arrangements.

10:01.734 --> 10:03.600
Come, Eugene.

10:03.736 --> 10:06.603
Are you the next of kin?

10:06.739 --> 10:09.140
No, we're making arrangements
for his mother.

10:09.275 --> 10:10.902
- Oh.
- I'll get her.

10:11.044 --> 10:12.273
Ah, his mother.

10:12.412 --> 10:15.848
Yes, the Widow Fonzarelli.

10:15.982 --> 10:17.973
MARION:
Come in, dear.

10:35.502 --> 10:37.470
Is this the guy that tried
to blow me up?

10:37.604 --> 10:39.732
Uh-huh.

10:44.277 --> 10:46.109
(in high-pitched voice):
Are you the man that is going

10:46.246 --> 10:50.149
to make the arrangements
for my son?

10:50.283 --> 10:52.650
Yes, it is, Widow Fonzarelli.

10:52.785 --> 10:54.275
That's nice.

10:54.420 --> 10:55.478
(shouts)

10:57.657 --> 10:58.886
Widow?

10:59.025 --> 11:01.119
Widow, cool it.

11:03.930 --> 11:06.991
<i>L</i> was SO overcome.

11:09.002 --> 11:10.663
If you'll walk this way, please.

11:10.803 --> 11:12.794
(muttering)

11:14.841 --> 11:17.276
As you can see,
we have a variety

11:17.410 --> 11:20.505
of caskets here
at Heavenly Slumber.

11:20.647 --> 11:22.877
I was a-thinking about something

11:23.016 --> 11:26.179
in the memory of Arturo
in leather.

11:26.319 --> 11:27.684
Leather?

11:27.820 --> 11:29.151
With a zipper.

11:32.559 --> 11:34.960
(muffled): If somebody
doesn't find us soon,

11:35.094 --> 11:37.085
we're gonna die!

11:45.972 --> 11:47.963
(women whispering)

11:55.515 --> 11:57.745
- Fonzie!
- Oh, please let us...

12:04.357 --> 12:05.586
It's incredible!

12:05.725 --> 12:07.989
Girls lined up as far
as the eye can see.

12:08.127 --> 12:09.959
This is the first funeral

12:10.096 --> 12:14.124
they ever had to have a,
uh, parade permit.

12:14.267 --> 12:15.325
Shh!

12:15.468 --> 12:17.061
(organ Ff laying)

12:17.203 --> 12:18.170
Let's do something.

12:18.304 --> 12:20.295
- Hm?
- Pay our respects.

12:24.210 --> 12:26.975
Oh, Howard, look,
they're so shiny and lifelike.

12:31.150 --> 12:32.481
Just think,

12:32.619 --> 12:34.917
I'll never hear
the word "Shortcake" again.

12:35.054 --> 12:38.024
Joanie,
it's just a pretend funeral.

12:38.157 --> 12:41.388
I know, but I don't want to let
a good funeral go to waste.

12:41.527 --> 12:44.019
Oh, Arthur, I'm gonna miss you.

12:44.163 --> 12:45.892
(crying): Remember the time
you missed dinner?

12:46.032 --> 12:47.090
I forgive you.

12:47.233 --> 12:48.496
- I didn't mean to be so upset.
- Marion...

12:48.635 --> 12:50.160
- And I loved doing your laundry.
- Marion!

12:50.303 --> 12:51.361
- I loved it!
- Sit down.

12:51.504 --> 12:53.495
(sobbing)

12:57.910 --> 12:59.605
You were terrific, Mrs. C.

12:59.746 --> 13:01.180
Thank you, Arthur.

13:01.314 --> 13:03.874
I feel much better.

13:06.052 --> 13:08.043
All right, keep looking.

13:10.056 --> 13:11.319
Psst!

13:11.457 --> 13:12.822
We've got to stall.

13:12.959 --> 13:14.427
So far we've searched
the premises,

13:14.560 --> 13:16.050
and we still can't locate
the printing press.

13:16.195 --> 13:18.493
When we do,
I'll give you the signal.

13:18.631 --> 13:19.689
Okay.

13:19.832 --> 13:21.493
Oh.

13:21.634 --> 13:22.692
What about Ralph and Potsie?

13:22.835 --> 13:23.996
You think they're gonna be okay?

13:24.137 --> 13:25.730
As long as they don't try
anything foolish.

13:25.872 --> 13:27.271
Oh.

13:27.407 --> 13:29.876
They're taking long enough.

13:30.009 --> 13:32.478
We don't want to miss
that 4:00 train.

13:32.612 --> 13:34.603
Hurry them up!

13:36.916 --> 13:38.315
We have to move it along.

13:38.451 --> 13:40.385
We have a lot of bodies waiting.

13:40.520 --> 13:43.251
EUGENE:
Let the mourners in.

13:45.158 --> 13:47.058
- Help!
