Help! Get me out of here.

13:57.704 --> 14:00.503
His boots look so peaceful.

14:00.640 --> 14:03.109
And the music's so fitting.

14:03.242 --> 14:05.711
All of Fonzie's favorite songs.

14:10.116 --> 14:12.813
(sobbing)

14:12.952 --> 14:16.217
Oh, Widow Fonzarelli,
I'm sorry that he...

14:16.356 --> 14:18.347
that he...

14:22.462 --> 14:24.521
It's a all right.

14:24.664 --> 14:26.860
We'll comfort each other.

14:28.334 --> 14:31.099
Oh, my, what strong arms
you have.

14:32.305 --> 14:35.002
(chuckles)
And what soft lips you have.

14:35.141 --> 14:37.769
It's all the better
to give you a kiss.

14:39.512 --> 14:42.243
Oh, you have lips like your son.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.248
It runs in the family.

14:44.384 --> 14:45.749
(sobbing continues)

14:45.885 --> 14:47.876
(gasps)

14:51.491 --> 14:52.617
That was a close one.

14:52.759 --> 14:54.523
- Will you stop it!
- Sorry.

15:04.771 --> 15:07.832
YEP, YEP, YEP, YEP-

15:11.310 --> 15:16.077
Oh, the Fonz was always
so good to me.

15:16.215 --> 15:18.616
(chuckles) I never really get
a chance to thank him.

15:18.751 --> 15:20.947
(choking up):
Me, too.

15:21.087 --> 15:24.022
We have to be brave
at a time like this.

15:24.157 --> 15:25.647
I know, I know.

15:25.792 --> 15:27.419
Oh, boy, I remember

15:27.560 --> 15:30.120
the very last things
he say to me.

15:30.263 --> 15:32.527
I was backing
out of the parking lot

15:32.665 --> 15:34.633
of Arnold's for the last time.

15:34.767 --> 15:36.861
The Fonz look at me and he say,

15:37.003 --> 15:40.633
"Don't run over my motorcycle!"

15:40.773 --> 15:43.265
(sobbing)

15:48.281 --> 15:50.841
Oh, that was beautiful.

15:50.983 --> 15:53.350
How's business, Al?

15:53.486 --> 15:55.545
Don't ask.

15:59.425 --> 16:01.450
RICHIE:
Come to pay your last respects,

16:01.594 --> 16:02.959
Officer Kirk?

16:03.095 --> 16:06.622
I came to make sure you buried
the troublemaking hood.

16:06.766 --> 16:07.699
Aaayyh ...

16:07.834 --> 16:09.768
(in high-pitched voice):
Aaayyh.

16:09.902 --> 16:11.802
Who's that?

16:11.938 --> 16:14.202
Uh, that's the Widow Fonzarelli.

16:23.616 --> 16:27.985
Thank you so much for a-coming
to my son's a-funeral.

16:28.120 --> 16:31.112
(groaning)

16:38.598 --> 16:39.724
Hey, Blue Eyes.

16:39.866 --> 16:41.265
What do you say
after the funeral,

16:41.400 --> 16:42.629
we go to a double feature?

16:42.768 --> 16:44.702
Me and me.

16:44.837 --> 16:48.102
I don't go to cartoon festivals.

17:12.431 --> 17:14.398
Well, Fonz,

17:14.534 --> 17:16.262
that was from the Big Ragoo
to you.

17:16.402 --> 17:18.871
I know that's the way you
would've wanted it.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.973
Pots, I said to the right.

17:26.112 --> 17:28.171
- This is the right.
- You're such a Potsie!

17:46.766 --> 17:49.565
Squigg, his boots died
with him off.

17:52.838 --> 17:54.567
I'm gonna miss you, Fonz.

17:54.707 --> 17:56.766
You was the nicest guy

17:56.909 --> 17:58.900
whatever beat me up.

18:04.550 --> 18:06.541
(Al sobbing)

18:10.256 --> 18:12.247
(sobbing)

18:28.341 --> 18:30.332
Where is he, Shirl?

18:32.278 --> 18:33.575
L-I don't know.

18:33.713 --> 18:35.147
Honestly.

18:35.281 --> 18:38.649
The big boss must have really
wanted him in a hurry, Laverne.

18:38.784 --> 18:40.411
Pulled him right
out of his boots.

18:40.553 --> 18:42.954
(sobbing continues)

18:43.089 --> 18:45.854
I'll never forget him.

18:45.992 --> 18:47.790
He was the only guy

18:47.927 --> 18:51.056
who ever hickeyed his initials
on my neck.

18:53.766 --> 18:55.495
That's so sweet.

18:55.635 --> 18:57.103
You can't keep
the boot, Laverne.

18:57.236 --> 18:59.000
- I want the boot.
- You can't keep the boot.

18:59.138 --> 19:01.197
- I want the boot. I want
the boot. -Drop the boot!

19:01.340 --> 19:03.331
(grunting)

19:08.981 --> 19:10.176
Listen to me, listen to me.

19:10.316 --> 19:12.478
Do you want Fonzie
to stand barefoot

19:12.618 --> 19:14.814
on that great stag line
in the sky, huh?

19:14.954 --> 19:17.423
No, he'd kill me.

19:19.925 --> 19:22.223
Oh, but I got
to leave him something, Shirl.

19:22.361 --> 19:23.988
Well, how about...

19:24.130 --> 19:25.029
No!

19:25.164 --> 19:26.359
You crazy?!

19:26.499 --> 19:27.989
My favorite sweater!

19:28.134 --> 19:29.932
No, no! No, are you nuts?

19:30.069 --> 19:31.730
This is a holy place!

19:31.871 --> 19:32.929
This is a holy place.

19:33.072 --> 19:34.403
But I want
to leave him something.

19:37.009 --> 19:39.000
There, that'll be enough.

19:41.480 --> 19:42.743
(sobbing continues)

19:42.882 --> 19:45.613
Good-bye, Fonzie's boots.

19:45.751 --> 19:47.913
Have a nice trip.

19:51.991 --> 19:53.982
Hello, Mr. Cunningham.

19:56.929 --> 20:00.832
Uh, this is
the Widow Fonzarelli.

20:04.036 --> 20:06.027
Does she know?

20:15.614 --> 20:17.139
We're very sorry.

20:17.283 --> 20:18.341
Yes.

20:51.050 --> 20:52.484
We're out of time, boss.

20:52.618 --> 20:55.883
CANDY MAN:
Finish this ceremony!

20:56.956 --> 20:58.583
Uh, no,

20:58.724 --> 20:59.714
we-we haven't sung a hymn yet.

20:59.859 --> 21:01.054
(all humming)

21:01.193 --> 21:02.251
Hymns are extra.

21:02.394 --> 21:03.361
Cut the hymns.

21:03.496 --> 21:06.193
Move out! Move out! Move out!

21:09.401 --> 21:11.301
One, two...

21:11.437 --> 21:12.734
Potsie?

21:12.872 --> 21:14.237
- Yeah.
- I said three, not two.

21:14.373 --> 21:16.432
Can't you even count?

21:16.575 --> 21:17.940
Would you stop yelling at me?

21:18.077 --> 21:19.704
I get excited and I can't think,

21:19.845 --> 21:24.339
so come on, let's just try it
one more time, okay?

21:24.483 --> 21:26.144
- Potsie?
- Hmm?

21:26.285 --> 21:28.413
How come your voice
isn't muffled like mine?

21:28.554 --> 21:30.921
Because I'm tired of talking
through this gag, that's why.

21:31.056 --> 21:32.148
I'm ti...

21:32.291 --> 21:34.020
Hey, Malph,

21:34.160 --> 21:36.458
Malph, my arm is free.

21:36.595 --> 21:39.189
Way to go, arm.

21:40.199 --> 21:43.134
(cackling)

21:47.973 --> 21:51.068
Well, it's too bad
you had to go, kid,

21:51.210 --> 21:53.269
but better you than us.

21:53.412 --> 21:55.471
So long, chump.

21:55.614 --> 21:58.083
(cackling)

21:59.618 --> 22:00.608
(gasps)

22:00.753 --> 22:02.847
(in high-pitched voice):
The chump lives.

22:02.988 --> 22:04.979
I've been had!

22:11.831 --> 22:14.493
Now, where are my buddies, huh?

22:14.633 --> 22:16.727
You balloon,
you don't give them to me soon,

22:16.869 --> 22:18.860
and I'm gonna pop you.

22:20.172 --> 22:21.537
- Fonz!
- Fonz!

22:21.674 --> 22:23.199
Fonz, we're out!

22:23.342 --> 22:25.003
- We got out!
- Wait a minute, hold it!

22:25.144 --> 22:26.134
How'd you do that?

22:26.278 --> 22:27.404
Oh, Fonz, it's great.

22:27.546 --> 22:29.571
All you got to do
is just sit here in the seat.

22:29.715 --> 22:32.844
It's great, we got to get
one of these at Arnold's, Fonz.

22:34.453 --> 22:36.717
That was a secret panel,
I understand, I understand.

22:36.856 --> 22:37.846
Sticky!

22:37.990 --> 22:39.981
Eugene!

22:40.993 --> 22:43.587
The mechanic... alive!

22:43.729 --> 22:45.959
You fool!
You fools, get him!

22:48.067 --> 22:49.728
- Come on.
- Come on.

22:49.869 --> 22:51.166
Come on!

22:51.303 --> 22:53.294
Make room for me.

22:56.842 --> 22:58.276
All right, let's go!

22:58.410 --> 23:00.071
(shouting)

23:00.212 --> 23:03.238
You found the printing press!

23:03.382 --> 23:04.543
Wait a second,
where's Fonzarelli?

23:04.683 --> 23:07.118
- With them.
- He can't handle the Candy Man.

23:07.253 --> 23:09.312
BOTH:
The Fonz can.

23:09.455 --> 23:12.049
(clattering)

23:13.192 --> 23:14.751
I knew he could do it.

23:14.894 --> 23:16.055
(thump)

23:17.062 --> 23:19.053
(laughter)

23:24.536 --> 23:25.469
Tell you something.

23:25.604 --> 23:27.265
Those creeps ate
all the marshmallows.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.397
(laughter)

23:40.286 --> 23:41.811
Hey, thanks very much.

23:41.954 --> 23:44.184
I'm sorry I had to put you
through this.

23:45.190 --> 23:47.022
Thanks for coming.

23:47.159 --> 23:49.924
Hey, I'm real sorry I had
to put you through this.

23:51.196 --> 23:53.062
Thanks for coming.

23:53.198 --> 23:54.632
I have an announcement to make.

23:54.767 --> 23:57.293
In honor of Fonzie being alive,

23:57.436 --> 24:00.633
